<section class="mageeat">
  <div class="mageeat-card">
    <span class="mageeat-role">About the Author</span>
    <h2>Talal Eddaouahiri — Founder of MoneyAbroadGuide</h2>
    <p>Talal Eddaouahiri is the founder of MoneyAbroadGuide.com. A Moroccan immigrant who settled in the United States in 2015, he has worked in retail banking, customer relations, and financial services, and has personally navigated the financial systems of the USA, Canada, Spain, and Morocco.</p>
    <p>He created MoneyAbroadGuide to help newcomers, immigrants, and international students navigate banking, credit building, money transfers, taxes, and personal finance in the USA and Canada.</p>
    <h3>Published Work</h3>
    <div class="mageeat-book"><strong>Author of:</strong> <em>Build Your Credit Score in the USA (2026 Edition)</em> — a complete, step-by-step guide for newcomers building a strong U.S. credit profile from scratch, even with no Social Security Number.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mageeat-card">
    <span class="mageeat-role">Editorial Standards</span>
    <h2>How We Research Our Guides</h2>
    <p>Recommending a financial product or strategy to a newcomer is a responsibility we take seriously. Every guide on MoneyAbroadGuide follows a structured research and verification process designed to keep our advice accurate, current, and genuinely useful.</p>
    <div class="mageeat-process">
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Research Process</h4><p>We map each topic against the real questions newcomers ask, then research it from the ground up using primary sources.</p></div>
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Fact Verification</h4><p>Every figure, fee, and requirement is checked against the official source before it is published.</p></div>
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Official Sources</h4><p>For SSN, ITIN, taxes, healthcare, and immigration details we rely on IRS, SSA, USCIS, and other federal and state sources.</p></div>
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Financial Institution Verification</h4><p>Bank fees and newcomer programs are confirmed directly against each institution's published terms.</p></div>
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Annual Updates</h4><p>Guides are reviewed and refreshed at least once a year — this page reflects 2026 data.</p></div>
      <div class="mageeat-step"><h4>Editorial Independence</h4><p>Our recommendations are never for sale. Affiliate partnerships never influence what we recommend or how we rank it.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
